title: What Next for Yes Bank? | CA Rachana Ranade | #shorts
description: Description:- In March 2020, a consortium of investors led by the State Bank of India infused Rs.10,000 Crore to bail out the bank. As a part of this, SBI bought shares worth Rs.6,050 Crores for a 48% stake. Further, as a part of the “Yes Bank Limited Reconstruction Scheme, 2020” shareholders holding more than 100 shares were locked in for 3 years for up to 75% of their shareholding, with SBI being required to hold a minimum of 26% during the lock-in period. SBI initially held 48.21%, which was reduced to 30% in June 2020 and 26.14% in December 2022. Currently, SBI is holding 26.14% worth Rs.12,402 crores. The lock-in period for SBI ended on March 6, 2023, and it has not sold any shares since then. The lock-in period for other stakeholders is ending on March 13, 2023. This is an important development in the banking industry and the future of Yes Bank. We will have to wait and see how this impacts the bank and its shareholders.

title: Reduce Your ELECTRICITY BILL by 90% | Finance With Sharan
description:
We humans pay so much for widely available resources- Land, Water, and Electricity. But in this video, we will talk about how to harness the power of the almighty Sun, to generate electricity for free. 
We also talk about how much money you can save, how many solar panels you need, and when you will break even the cost of installing the solar panels. 
Watch till the end to know step by step procedure of getting solar panels and saving on a huge chunk of money. 

Models used:
1. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/11aHaXbB09uFlftngCrBriJZqvvzq6yQB/export?format=xlsx

Connect with me:

Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/financewithsharan/
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/financewithsharan
LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/sharanhegde95/ 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/financewsharan

#financewithsharan #finance #sharan
tags: ['finance with sharan', 'finance with sharan earning', 'solar panels', 'solar panel price', 'solar panel for home', 'is solar pannel really worth it in india', 'are solar panels worth it', 'subsidy on solar panels 2022', 'subsidy on solar panels 2023', 'solar square energy', 'solar energy', 'solar energy explained', 'solar power', 'pros and cons of solar energy', 'advantages of solar energy']
Comments: ['I am from Tamilnadu and have installed solar panels 5 years before....Had good times till last year regarding reduction of EB bills.... For the last one year the TNEB started charging money for the units what we generate and transmit up and down through their network... Now I am paying a lot which is almost equal to the previous bills before installing solar panels... The government should actually encourage people to install solar panels rather than taxing more and more who have already installed', 'Great video !Additional points :1. The plant capacity installed should be less than or equal to the permitted load from DISCOMs.2. Metering are of two types, Net and Gross. For high self consumption, net meter are suitable and for low consumption gross can be opted, however the ROI of gross is more based on current export rates.Correction : The panels are rated for kWp and not kWh .', 'For people who are getting Load Penalty in their electricity bill i have a tip#if you are using more units than alloted increase kW like 1.5kW to 2kW#use only one appliance at a timeExample: turn off  refrigerator while using washing machineI have TV, Refrigerator and Washing machine at home and i reduced bill amount from ₹800 to ₹600 by increasing kW from 1.5 to 2 and following above steps.Also replace any CFL bulb , tubelight and old 100 candle bulb with LED bulbs.', 'WhoaHatsoff to the kind of knowledge you share, Mr.Sharan  Thank you for this insightful video ️🇮🇳', 'You nailed it bro...complex content explained with so ease. The only con which i think is the payback period which is roughly 4 to 7 years depending upon the system and insurance is a must in storm prone areas. Goverment policies keeps changing for ongrid premium that can make the investment risky.', 'Your energy is on another level bro really useful info to make the world a better place ', 'In Bengaluru, there is fixed charges. For 3KW connection(usually 2 bhk independent house gets 3KW) 330 rs is fixed charge which is like even 0 reading we need to pay 330rs.', 'Awesome video with full throttle...enjoyed a lot.Sharan, In Gujarat, the generated unit is purchased by GRID at 2.45/2.75 INR, while GEB charges 5/7INR per unit.', 'Have had solar panels installed on my rooftop almost 6 years ago now and I get money from BESCOM for additional units sent into the grid. Also, zero maintenance till date. Haven’t had any issues at all', 'Bro please make a video on  career in finance. Which courses to do after 12th should we do MBA further. And how to get a good job. I am sure you will make video soon to help us ', "No one talks about the vulnerability to the panels by storms and hail stones, literally it hailed yesterday in our city and many people's panels were broken, because it's glass, and glass breaks ....", 'Cons is just the initial investment cost. But the prose outweigh the cons by a big margin. My average bill used to be rs. 4000 rupees to 5000 rupees for 2 months which got reduced to 200 to 300 rupees.', '"Things work out best for those who make the best of how things work out." ---John Wooden', 'Installed the 3kW system in last January, it was insatlled and ready to use in 3-4 days but we were not able to use it because discomm were taking months to approve the net meter, it took them 2-3 months to approve and install the meter, had to bribe to get this done.Since then our bills have reduced to almost 10% of previous amount, our roof is much cooler since they are under constant shade of solar panel. So apart from that department issues everything is fine.', 'Simple solution: shut everything and no electricity bill ', 'Fun Fact : When you realise you lack space for installing a solar panel when you live in skyscrapper with 150 flats . Also people living in small houses can also face problem when their surroundings get filled up with multi storied buildings which will block sunlight form entering your house .', 'Awesome video Sharan.Really good info..', 'Thanks to your awareness in reducing electricity bill and also step forward to renewable energy sources', 'I had discussed about it and they had said that,after when the electricity is gone,The MSEB Stores the electricity made by Solar and gives it to us at that time.', 'Sharan i use on grid system one another saving is cooking gas im now totally using induction cooker and saving a lot on cooking gas also there would be much more savings if we use an Ev', 'Just keep in mind that the maintenance battery is not included.The battery has a very low performance. The number of charge and discharge cycles is restricted. The battery must be replaced every 5 years. You must invest around Rs40,000.', "I was sure subscribing to Sharan's channel wouldn't go waste. Comments: ['In November 2022 I was using my phone at least 9 hrs per day but after watching your contents and reading self building books .Now, I use my phone only 2 hrs a day and spending time with family, doing my hobbies and studying.I think I am transforming to the person that I always wanted to be .Big Thanks to you ️For being here for us.', '1 . Digital minimalism2. Define core values3. Digital declutter4. Spend time alone5. Practice to adopt6.summary', "Minimalism 1. Define your core values 2. Digital Declutter3. Practices to adopt3.1 leave your phone at home3.2  take long walks 3.3 write letters to yourself 3.4 reclaim leisure 3.5 imagine you have to pay for every click , swip.3.6 lessen your availabilityWriting these to keep them in my mind for long term because it's a way of revision", "Summary of Digital minimilsm  video- 1. Define ur core values- It can be Friendship, Truth, Religion etc.1.1 Wt is most imp thing u wanna achieve? Do u spend ur time for that?2. Digital declutter- 2.1 Stop using all non-essential apps & tech's for 30 days & Use only supportive tech's  which helps ur values in the best way. 2.2 Work on ur hobbies3. title: EP : 01 - How to Generate Best Stock ideas Everyday.
description:
Welcome to Finology Quest Classes, Season 2.
In this video, we will be exploring how to pick stocks by using screeners and bundles of Ticker. If you're new to the world of investing, it can be overwhelming to know where to start when it comes to picking good stocks. But fear not, we're here to guide you through the process!

By the end of this video, you'll have a better understanding of how to pick good and quality stocks, as well as some key factors to consider when evaluating potential investments. With this knowledge, you'll be better equipped to navigate the stock market and make informed investment decisions.

title: The Big Mac Index Hota Kya Hai? 🍔
description:
Have you ever wondered what the cost of an item you consume in India 🇮🇳 would be abroad?

 If you have traveled abroad, you would have noticed that the price of the same goods varies between countries. 

For example, a Big Mac 🍔 costs 5$ approx. in the US, which is equivalent to INR. 400. However, the cost of the same burger in India is just INR. 250. Do the math and you get 1$ coming to just INR 50 INR compared to the INR 80 exchange rate. 

This is because the Big mac is cheaper to produce in India. The cost of rent, salaries etc., are much more affordable in India than in the US 🇺🇸, even though they produce the same burger. 

This is called the Big Mac Index, where the cost of big macs is used to determine the purchasing power parity (PPP).

The PPP compares the value of all goods and services produced between 2 countries and ensures them with one another. By comparing PPP, we can compare income from different countries concerning your spending power. For context, the PPP between the US and India is 1$ = INR 22. 

✅ So the next time you are chowing down on a burger, remember this reel and that you’d have paid more for the same burger somewhere else.

title: 11-year-old Reyan's impressive defence against Grandmaster | Delhi GM 2023
description:
Reyan Md. (1818) is a young talent from Bihar, India. After winning the National Schools u-11 championship in May 2022, he has been performing consistently and has increased by more than 200 rating points. At the 20th Delhi International Grandmaster Open 2023 he faced GM Vitaly Teterev (2377) and his impressive defence earned him half a point, Watch the interview as he talks about the game and also how his life has been after becoming the National Schools champion.

Video:  Aditya Sur Roy / ChessBase India

title: A beautiful gesture by Magnus after the game | Carlsen vs Nepo | Commentary by Sagar
description:

It was an unbelievably intense game with Nepo putting immense pressure on Carlsen. But how did the game end? It ended with a very nice gesture by the World Champion. title: How Hospitals Are SCAMMING YOU
description:
Don’t you get the feeling that there is little difference left between five star hotels 🌟 and the so-called state-of-the-art hospitals?

Both give five star service, and if you are not aware, these hospitals charge a bomb & too, sometimes even double the average cost. 💣 

Yes, you guessed it right. 

The insurance companies don’t like it. * They put a clause called “US” or “usual, reasonable and customary” clause. ❎ 

Meaning, they will only cover the average cost for that kind of procedure in your geographical area.

A difference of 10-20% percentage is fine, but not beyond that. This is why so many claims get settled only partially. ( And it is difficult to fight for the exorbitant cost that the hospital charged you. 🏥 

➡️ So next time you have a planned procedure, make sure to have a rough estimate as to how much such a procedure costs in your area. You can then choose the hospital accordingly !

#financewithsharan #healthinsurance #insurancetips #insuranceagent #lifeinsurance #moneytalks #moneymotivated

title: 16-year-old super talent vs 59-year-old super coach | Michal Krasenkow vs Volodar Murzin
description:
GM Michał Krasenkow is one of the finest trainers and writers in the world of chess. He has trained some of the best players in the world. His aggressive style of playing is something that made him one of the best. In round eight of the 20th Delhi International Grandmaster Open 2023, he faced the very strong and talented GM Michal Krasenkow. title: Send Money Internationally Without Banks Or Foreign Exchange
description:
Humans have been using paper for money starting from the early 7th century. But of late, crypto-currencies have seen a rise. 🔐

The government is not a huge fan of crypto due to the lack of regulation, so they made their very own crypto called e-RUPI, and here’s what it means for us. 

An e-RUPI is a digital token equivalent to our fiat currency i.e., the Indian Rupee. ₹₹₹

Since they are digital money, the cost and speed of transactions are vastly reduced, ensuring seamless service over long distances at a cheaper cost 💸

An added advantage of digitizing money is that you can program it to ensure it is utilized only for a given purpose. The government can utilize this feature to ensure that the money goes to the scheme as planned and not elsewhere. However, there is a fear that the government can program the money to monitor the public and control our spending. 

➡️ As uncle Ben said, with great power comes great responsibility. Tell me in the comments below if we are ready for CBDCs or not. 

#financewithsharan #moneytalks #moneymotivated .
#theonepercentclub #erupi #cryptonews #moneytalks #bank #rbi

title: Proposing On A Budget
description:
Who says size matters, well maybe it does, but not to the extent you are thinking of. 

First, get your mind out of the gutter, and let me explain. 

Diamond engagement rings 💍 are all the rage nowadays, but diamonds are not cheap. Getting a diamond ring for your missus could very well empty your bank. 

Now you can’t bail on your fiance’s request for a diamond ring, but you can get one cheaper than advertised. 🤩

Rather than purchasing a 1-carat diamond ring, get a ring for 0.9 carats instead. The costs of a diamond depend on the 4C’s the cut, clarity, color, and carat. 

The best-looking diamonds have the best cut and clarity, which is what you should be looking for, carat is just the size of the diamond. The naked eye 👁️ can barely pick the difference between a 0.9 and 1-carat diamond, but the difference in cost can be upwards of 30% and more. 

So getting a 0.9 carat can save you a bunch of money while still impressing your fiancé 👩‍❤️‍👨
.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.

title: How Banks Are SCAMMING YOU!!!
description:
You go to a bank 🏦 for home loan. You are somewhat tensed as this is a very big decision. 

You have heard a lot about interest rates rising, and in turn home loan loan EMI or tenure increasing. 😱

The loan official knows what is best for his bank! He is doing this job every single day, so obviously there is information assymetry. 🤨

Sensing your discomfort with EMIs rising in the future, he pitches a fixed rate home loan. 😒 You are told that you need not worry about changing rates as the interest will be charged at a fixed rate for this loan.

You may ask - so what Sharan? If my outgo is fixed, I will have a good night’s sleep. What’s wrong with that?

Well, there are no free lunches! The “fixed” rate may be fixed only for a fixed duration  and may be revised under the “reset” cause in future. Maybe in the event of sharp interest rate hikes or even periodically say once in x years. 🥺

➡️ TL;DR - Please read your terms and conditions while signing off a home loan. Devil 😈 is always in the detail!

If something looks too good to be true, it probably is! 😇
.

.
.
.
.

title: Buy or Rent ? The FINAL ANSWER.
description:

In this video, we'll dive into the pros and cons of buying vs renting a home and dispel some of the common myths perpetuated by influencers. 

Don't fall for half-truths and misinformation. Watch this video to get the full picture of whether buying or renting a house is right for you and how real estate also can be a solid investment option for your financial future.

He provides insights into the initiatives taken by various organizations and governments to raise awareness about millets and encourages viewers to embrace millets as a part of their regular diet.

** A differential equation of first order and first degree can be written as f( x, y, dy/dx) = 0.
* For any differential equations it is possible to find the general solution and particular solution.
* If in an equation it is possible to collect all the terms of x and dx on one side and all the terms of y and dy on the other side, then the variables are said to be separable. Thus the general form of such an equation is,
f(x)dx = g(y)dy (or) f(x)dx + g(y)dy = 0.

In this video we talk about how we neglect our health, and what it can cost us.

* If in an equation it is possible to collect all the terms of x and dx on one side and all the terms of y and dy on the other side, then the variables are said to be separable. Thus the general form of such an equation is,
f(x)dx = g(y)dy (or) f(x)dx + g(y)dy = 0.

** A differential equation of first order and first degree can be written as f( x, y, dy/dx) = 0.
* For any differential equations it is possible to find the general solution and particular solution.
* If in an equation it is possible to collect all the terms of x and dx on one side and all the terms of y and dy on the other side, then the variables are said to be separable. Thus the general form of such an equation is,
f(x)dx = g(y)dy (or) f(x)dx + g(y)dy = 0.

title: What is Clean Plant Program ? Geography & Environment Current Affairs by Sudarshan Gurjar | UPSC
description:
In this video, educator Sudarshan Gurjar discusses the Union Government's plan to launch an Atmanirbhar Clean Plant Program for the horticulture industry. 
The program, which is expected to be launched soon, aims to promote clean and sustainable practices in horticulture to reduce pollution and environmental damage.
He provides an overview of the horticulture industry in India and the challenges it faces in terms of pollution and sustainability. 
He then discusses the various initiatives under the Atmanirbhar Clean Plant Program that are aimed at promoting clean and sustainable practices in horticulture, such as the use of precision farming techniques and reducing the use of harmful pesticides and fertilizers.
Throughout the video, He offers insights into the potential impact of the program on the horticulture industry, including the benefits for farmers, consumers, and the environment. 
He also discusses the challenges that may arise in implementing the program, such as the need for greater government support and investment in new technologies.
Whether you're a farmer, industry professional, or simply interested in sustainable practices in horticulture, this video provides valuable insights into the upcoming Atmanirbhar Clean Plant Program and its potential impact on the industry. 
So tune in and join the conversation on promoting clean and sustainable horticulture practices in India!
